title: Bound Print
medium: Letterpress, etching and aquatint, brush and watercolor on white wove paper mounted on heavy cream board, lines ruled in color and gold paint
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of the Council
description: Interior of large ballroom with several pink and yellow chandeliers in shape of upturned blossoms. Drapes are blue on right; wall coverings are red with gold foliage; decorative green pagodas stand at each window on right and flank fireplace on left. Dozens of men and women are gathered seated and standing along the walls as an orchestra plays.
